  reply: 'Welcome to the lesson on measuring electrical quantities. \n' +
    '\n' +
    'In this session, we’re going to focus on getting you comfortable with identifying and selecting the right measurement instruments for the job. By the end of this, you’ll be able to choose the correct tool for measuring current, voltage, resistance, power, and energy.\n' +
    '\n' +
    "It’s one of the most practical parts of the Level 2 course because using the wrong instrument doesn't just lead to a wrong reading—it can easily damage your meter or the circuit itself.\n" +
    '\n' +
    'We’re going to run through this in four short chunks:\n' +
    '1. Measuring Current and Voltage\n' +
    '2. Measuring Resistance\n' +
    '3. Measuring Power and Energy\n' +
    '4. Instrument Selection Logic\n' +
    '\n' +
    "After each part, I’ll ask you a quick question to make sure we're on the right track before moving to the next bit.\n" +
    '\n' +
    "Let me know when you're ready to start with current and voltage.",
