  lessonSectionPhase: 'teach',
  reply: "When we're out on site, we need to be clear about exactly what we are measuring before we even pick up our test leads. If you want to check the flow of electricity through a circuit, you are looking for the current. This is measured in Amperes—usually just called Amps—and you'll need an ammeter for this. Crucially, the ammeter has to be connected so that the current actually flows through the device.\n" +
    '\n' +
    'On the other hand, if you are checking the electrical pressure or the potential difference between two specific points, you are measuring voltage. For this, you use a voltmeter, which measures across those two points. A common mistake is thinking a multimeter handles everything automatically, but you must manually select the right function to ensure you get an accurate reading and keep your equipment safe.\n' +
    '\n' +
    '1. Which specific instrument is used to measure the flow of electrical current in a circuit?\n' +
    '2. Which instrument is used to measure the electrical potential difference between two points?\n' +
    '3. What is the specific SI unit measured by an ammeter?',
